SANJEEV KAPOOR: Hold on,
I don't get paid so much.

00:32:16.870 --> 00:32:17.370
[LAUGHTER]

00:32:17.370 --> 00:32:18.870
SANJEEV KAPOOR: I'm
still highly underpaid.

00:32:18.870 --> 00:32:20.000
APRAJITA JAIN: You should call
your accountant at present

00:32:20.000 --> 00:32:20.470
and ask what's going on.

00:32:20.470 --> 00:32:21.678
SANJEEV KAPOOR: What is this?

00:32:21.678 --> 00:32:23.000
What's going on?

00:32:23.000 --> 00:32:24.972
I feel highly underpaid now.

00:32:24.972 --> 00:32:26.328
[LAUGHTER]

00:32:26.328 --> 00:32:27.232
APRAJITA JAIN: And this
is just some of them.

00:32:27.232 --> 00:32:29.565
SANJEEV KAPOOR: Yeah, and I
was working on weekend also.

00:32:29.565 --> 00:32:30.870
What is this?

00:32:30.870 --> 00:32:31.370
Not fair.

00:32:31.370 --> 00:32:32.060
[CHUCKLES]

00:32:32.060 --> 00:32:33.518
APRAJITA JAIN: So
how do you do all

00:32:33.518 --> 00:32:36.812
of that and doing justice to
all of them at the same time?

00:32:36.812 --> 00:32:38.020
SANJEEV KAPOOR: I don't know.

00:32:38.020 --> 00:32:39.880
I don't think
about these things.

00:32:39.880 --> 00:32:40.930
I just do it.

00:32:40.930 --> 00:32:43.630
I don't
over-intellectualize things.

00:32:43.630 --> 00:32:47.140
I think I just take
one day at a time.

00:32:47.140 --> 00:32:53.860
And I say that this is the
most important thing now.

00:32:53.860 --> 00:32:55.660
APRAJITA JAIN: Mhm,
be in the moment.

00:32:55.660 --> 00:32:56.535
SANJEEV KAPOOR: Yeah.

00:32:56.535 --> 00:33:00.160
So that's how I deal with it.

00:33:00.160 --> 00:33:06.670
And you can only do it if you
have a great team with you,

00:33:06.670 --> 00:33:13.120
starting with my wife, to all
our activities and everything

00:33:13.120 --> 00:33:15.810
that we do.

00:33:15.810 --> 00:33:18.160
So you mentioned
about Indian railways.

00:33:18.160 --> 00:33:22.510
There's a big meeting in
Delhi with the team of Railway

00:33:22.510 --> 00:33:24.220
Ministry and everyone.

00:33:24.220 --> 00:33:28.906
So one of our chefs has
traveled from Mumbai.

00:33:28.906 --> 00:33:32.759
Actually, I had suggested that,
because we have chefs in Delhi,

00:33:32.759 --> 00:33:33.550
somebody come down.

00:33:33.550 --> 00:33:36.189
No, no, we want to
send someone senior.

00:33:36.189 --> 00:33:36.980
We want to do that.

00:33:36.980 --> 00:33:39.030
I said, OK, fine,
whatever you want to do.

00:33:39.030 --> 00:33:41.187
So we have a good--

00:33:41.187 --> 00:33:43.270
APRAJITA JAIN: So you have
a good network of chefs

00:33:43.270 --> 00:33:44.510
that can also pitch in--

00:33:44.510 --> 00:33:46.210
SANJEEV KAPOOR:
At our company, we

00:33:46.210 --> 00:33:54.310
are fortunate to have good
people, talented, good value

00:33:54.310 --> 00:33:54.810
system.

00:33:54.810 --> 00:33:58.130
That's very, very
important to us.

00:33:58.130 --> 00:34:03.140
So yeah, I think because
of that, it just happens.

